net.ontopia.topicmaps.query.sparql.impl.sesame
Class SparqlTurtleResultHandler

java.lang.Object
  net.ontopia.topicmaps.query.sparql.impl.sesame.SparqlTurtleResultHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
OntopiaResultHandler<java.util.List<java.lang.String[]>>, org.openrdf.rio.RDFHandler
public class SparqlTurtleResultHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.openrdf.rio.RDFHandler, OntopiaResultHandler<java.util.List<java.lang.String[]>>

This class receives namespaces, RDF statements and comments in process of evaluating SPARQL CONSTRUCT query form.

In the first phase the RDF statements are collected via push methods (handle* methods). Result document is created on the go, and its statements are written compactly.

In the second phase the result document can be obtain via get methods.

Handler implements two interfaces. One for OpenRDF side (RDFHandler) and one for Ontopia side ( OntopiaResultHandler)

private java.lang.String getLiteral(org.openrdf.model.Literal literal)
Returns provided Literal in Turtle notation.

Long strings are encoded as """Turtle long strings""". Returned string consist of literal's label (the value) and optionally ^^datatype or @lang suffix (not both).

Parameters:

Returns:
string representation of provided literal.

Returns:
